fredr
  • Reference

Send a request to the FRED API

Send a request to the FRED API

fredr(endpoint, ..., to_frame = TRUE, print_req = FALSE)

Arguments

endpoint

A character vector of length 1 representing the FRED API path of interest. See https://api.stlouisfed.org/docs/fred/ for a list of endpoint possible values.
...

A series of paramters to be used in the query. Of the form param_key = 'param_value'. Acceptable parameters are specific to the API path. See https://api.stlouisfed.org/docs/fred/ for a list of recognized parameters for each endpoint.
to_frame

A boolean value indicating whether or not the response should be parsed and formatted as a data.frame. Default is TRUE.
print_req

A boolean value indicating whether or not the request should be printed as well. Useful for debugging. Default is FALSE.

Value

If to_frame = TRUE, a data.frame containing the parsed response. If to_frame = FALSE, an object returned directly from httr::GET().

Examples

 fredr(endpoint = "series/observations",
       series_id = "GNPCA",
       observation_start = "1990-01-01",
       observation_end = "2000-01-01")
#> # A tibble: 11 x 4

 not_run({
   library(httr)
   library(tidyverse)
   resp <- fredr(endpoint = "series/observations",
                 series_id = "GNPCA",
                 observation_start = "1990-01-01",
                 observation_end = "2000-01-01",
                 to_frame = FALSE)
   data <- resp %>%
     httr::content() %>%
     .$observations %>%
     purrr::map_df(.f = function(x) tibble::as_tibble(x = x))
})
